<TITLE> Switzerland pledges more aid </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 28 (bdnews24.com)Switzerland has pledged an additional US $ 3 lakh for the cyclone-hit people of Bangladesh as an emergency response, bringing the total Swiss assistance to US $ 4 lakh 60 thousand. The additional US$ 300,000 would be used to provide food, clothes, and temporary shelter materials to the cyclone affected people in Khulna and Bagerhat districts. The relief materials will be distributed through 2 local NGOs --Rupantar and Ashroy. An expert from the Swiss government's humanitarian aid division is expected to arrive in Bangladesh soon to extend support in the relief operation. Meanwhile, a fresh shipment of US relief materials, including four water purification treatment units (each capable of meeting daily water requirements of 10 thousand people), four 10 thousand- litre water storage units, 2,400 jerry-cans, and 10,000 blankets, arrived Dhaka Wednesday. Secretary to the ministry of Food and Disaster Management, Dr. Mohammad Ayub Miah, U.S. Embassy charge d' affaires, Geeta Pasi, and US Agency for International Development director, Denise Rollins visited Zia International Airport Wednesday. The relief materials will be flown by US military C-130 aircraft to Barisal. b
